# 0.1 - Quick Start

This is a set of short examples with minimal explanation. It is meant as
a "quick start".


Add a file to udfs:

  echo "hello world" >hello
  udfs add hello


View it:

  udfs cat <the-hash-you-got-here>


Try a directory:

  mkdir foo
  mkdir foo/bar
  echo "baz" > foo/baz
  echo "baz" > foo/bar/baz
  udfs add -r foo


View things:

  udfs ls <the-hash-here>
  udfs ls <the-hash-here>/bar
  udfs cat <the-hash-here>/baz
  udfs cat <the-hash-here>/bar/baz
  udfs cat <the-hash-here>/bar
  udfs ls <the-hash-here>/baz


References:

  udfs refs <the-hash-here>
  udfs refs -r <the-hash-here>
  udfs refs --help


Get:

  udfs get <the-hash-here> -o foo2
  diff foo foo2


Objects:

  udfs object get <the-hash-here>
  udfs object get <the-hash-here>/foo2
  udfs object --help


Pin + GC:

  udfs pin add <the-hash-here>
  udfs repo gc
  udfs ls <the-hash-here>
  udfs pin rm <the-hash-here>
  udfs repo gc


Daemon:

  udfs daemon  (in another terminal)
  udfs id


Network:

  (must be online)
  udfs swarm peers
  udfs id
  udfs cat <hash-of-remote-object>


Mount:

  (warning: fuse is finicky!)
  udfs mount
  cd /udfs/<the-hash-here>
  ls


Tool:

  udfs version
  udfs update
  udfs commands
  udfs config --help
  open http://localhost:5001/webui


Browse:

  webui:

    http://localhost:5001/webui

  video:

    http://localhost:8080/udfs/QmVc6zuAneKJzicnJpfrqCH9gSy6bz54JhcypfJYhGUFQu/play#/udfs/QmTKZgRNwDNZwHtJSjCp6r5FYefzpULfy37JvMt9DwvXse

  images:

    http://localhost:8080/udfs/QmZpc3HvfjEXvLWGQPWbHk3AjD5j8NEN4gmFN8Jmrd5g83/cs

  markdown renderer app:

    http://localhost:8080/udfs/QmX7M9CiYXjVeFnkfVGf3y5ixTZ2ACeSGyL1vBJY1HvQPp/mdown
